A non-conference for creatives, @epicurrence is all about building connections, sharing experiences, and finding inspiration in the fresh mountain air. This year a few of us trekked through Yosemite at the Epicurrence Summer Revival and came back completely reenergized with new friends and stories to share. Thank you to the Epicurrence team for creating such a wonderful week.

Happy 826 Day! @826valencia is a nonprofit organization dedicated to supporting under-resourced students in San Francisco with their writing skills. We feel honored to have been able to partner with them on the redesign of their website that launched earlier this week. Check out their new site at www.826valencia.org and if you can, donate or volunteer to support them! .

We want to welcome Adrien, our second design intern from HETIC this year (we love @instahetic )! Adrien was born and raised in Paris, France. This is his first time being in San Francisco and America and he’s loving how nice and friendly everyone is. He enjoys playing guitar, dancing, and all things Michael Jackson — his brother even posted a Youtube video of him moonwalking (we are actively trying to find this link). We’re super excited to have Adrien and his dancing skills here! Welcome to San Francisco and Upperquad, Adrien!

Join us as we give a big shoutout to Evan, our new Art Director! Originally from Washington DC, Evan spent the last 3 years in Venice, California working in advertising and enjoying the LA weather before making his way up to the Bay. He's a seasoned traveler and has already visited over 32 countries. He loves photography and playing piano — a skill that he first taught himself at just 10 years old. We are thrilled to have him here and can't wait to show you his amazing photography and design work. Welcome, Evan! @evancorrigan
